headlines.description: — Shake Milton scored 27 points, Dwight Howard had 18 points and 15 rebounds, and the Philadelphia 76ers finished a six-game road trip without injured star center Joel Embiid by beating the Cleveland Cavaliers 114-94 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sixers end trip without Embiid by beating Cavs 114-94

headlines.description: — Josh Jackson scored 19 of his season-high 31 points in the first half and the Detroit Pistons went on to rout the Washington Wizards 120-91 on Thursday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson has season-high 31 as Pistons rout Wizards

headlines.description: — Jeff Green outscored Charlotte by himself in Brooklyn's overpowering first quarter before finishing with 21 points, and the Nets got a strong debut from LaMarcus Aldridge in a 111-89 rout of the Hornets on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets get strong debut from Aldridge, rout Hornets 111-89

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Victor Oladipo finally made his Miami debut, and the Heat ensured it was a memorable one.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oladipo makes his debut, Heat top Warriors 116-109

events.name: Orlando Magic at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Terrence Ross hit two key jumpers late in overtime, Wendell Carter III scored 21 points and the Orlando Magic beat the short-handed New Orleans Pelicans 115-110 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ross lifts Magic over short-handed Pelicans in overtime

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Clint Capela had 28 points and 17 rebounds, Trae Young had 28 points and 12 assists, and the Atlanta Hawks overcame two late meltdowns to beat the San Antonio Spurs 134-129 in double overtime Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Capela, Young guide Hawks past Spurs 134-129 in 2 OT

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray scored 23 points and the Denver Nuggets led all the way in beating the Los Angeles Clippers 101-94 on Thursday night for their fourth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nuggets lead all the way in beating Clippers 101-94
